Company Vacation Policy

Effective Date: January 1, 2024

1. Vacation Accrual
All full-time employees accrue vacation time at a rate of 2 weeks per year for the first 3 years of employment. After 3 years, the accrual rate increases to 3 weeks per year.

2. Vacation Usage
- Vacation time can be used in minimum increments of 4 hours
- Employees must request vacation at least 2 weeks in advance
- Vacation requests are subject to manager approval
- Maximum of 2 consecutive weeks can be taken at one time

3. Vacation Carryover
Unused vacation time can be carried over to the next year, up to a maximum of 40 hours. Any vacation time exceeding 40 hours will be forfeited on December 31st.

4. Vacation Payout
Upon termination of employment, employees will be paid for any accrued but unused vacation time, up to the maximum carryover limit.

5. Holiday Policy
The company observes 10 paid holidays per year:
- New Year's Day
- Martin Luther King Jr. Day  
- Presidents' Day
- Memorial Day
- Independence Day
- Labor Day
- Thanksgiving Day
- Day after Thanksgiving
- Christmas Eve
- Christmas Day

If a holiday falls on a weekend, it will be observed on the nearest weekday.

6. Sick Leave
Employees accrue 1 sick day per month, up to a maximum of 12 days per year. Sick leave does not carry over to the next year and is not paid out upon termination.

For questions about this policy, contact HR at hr@company.com or extension 1234. 